EFFLUENTS AND WASTE

Linked to our goal of water conservation is that of reducing and managing waste, as improper disposal could also lead to pollution of clean water sources, amongst other environmental damages.

In our operations, waste management efforts are focused on the by-products generated by the manufacturing process in our factories.

OUR APPROACH

Soya pulp residue, also known as okara, is a byproduct from our soy milk production. Traditionally disposed in the landfills, okara can also be used as animal feed or as natural fertilisers.

Currently, our okara waste from the Malaysia factories are sold off as animal feed to the farms in the vicinity. In the Singapore factory, we dispose it to an offtaker who uses the by-product as fertilisers while maintaining dialogues with agencies to explore alternative usage for okara.
